# Corvus Sentinel environment
# Expo only exposes vars prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_ to app code.
#
# SECURITY: never put a secret in an EXPO_PUBLIC_* var — they are baked into the
# APK and are trivially extractable. Only non-secret values (URLs, flags) belong
# here. API keys live server-side in ocws-site (process.env), behind proxies.

# Corvus voice (ElevenLabs) is synthesized SERVER-SIDE. The ElevenLabs key is
# held by ocws-site (ELEVENLABS_API_KEY) behind /api/elevenlabs/speak — it is NOT
# bundled in the app. Override the proxy URL below only for non-prod backends.
# Locked Corvus voice ID Oq6YjhFgak69fZQyDSCd is selected on the server.
EXPO_PUBLIC_CORVUS_TTS_URL=

# Shared specimen library endpoint (POST target for auto-uploaded unknown-build
# captures). Leave blank to keep specimens on-device only until the backend
# exists. Expected to accept a JSON specimen body.
EXPO_PUBLIC_CORVUS_LIBRARY_URL=

# Shared FINDINGS endpoint (fleet sync). When a device has a network it POSTs
# queued contact findings here and GETs peers' (?since=<ms>) so every device
# converges on the same picture -- offline-first, ungated. Leave blank for a
# fully air-gapped deployment (findings just queue locally / P2P mesh only).
# POST body: { reports: string[] }  ·  GET returns: { reports: string[] }
EXPO_PUBLIC_CORVUS_FINDINGS_URL=
